description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Healthcare Assistant &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for experienced and dynamic Band 2 health care assistants to work at the newly established Haven unit at Meadowfield.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will need to demonstrate excellent interpersonal skills, an ability to be flexible in response to the acute care services, have an understanding and respectful approach to the needs of people presenting with mental health needs and be able to work under the direction and alongside the trained staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking into getting the team established and will love to hear from anyone who can demonstrate enthusiasm and willingness to learn what the ethos of the unit is and work towards the same goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Gina Wilson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address gina.wilson@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0300 3040787&lt;/p&gt;
